            <title>[JCR-3229] FileRevision should have a flag to control whether to sync the file on every write.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-3229</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>FileRevision class syncs the underlying revision.log file it uses on every write which could be a performance problem. Add a boolean flag to control whether to sync the file on every write.</description>
