                    <comment id="13202264" author="meteatamel" created="Tue, 7 Feb 2012 12:01:42 +0000"  >`</comment>
                    <comment id="13202265" author="meteatamel" created="Tue, 7 Feb 2012 12:02:20 +0000"  >Proposed fix.</comment>
                    <comment id="13202417" author="dpfister" created="Tue, 7 Feb 2012 14:24:33 +0000"  >Hi Mete,&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks for providing a patch. I noticed that you changed both FileJournal&amp;#39;s and DatabaseJournal&amp;#39;s revision.log to not sync after writing (opposed to the current state where they sync after every write), which might result in information loss if that cluster node crashes before the file system will eventually write changes back to disk. Don&amp;#39;t you think this might be problematic?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Kind regards&lt;br/&gt;
Dominique</comment>
                    <comment id="13202424" author="meteatamel" created="Tue, 7 Feb 2012 14:30:07 +0000"  >Ah yes. I meant to keep the default sync on but only provide a way to turn it off if someone wanted it. So, you&amp;#39;re right, my mistake, both journal should sync by default as before.</comment>
                    <comment id="13202449" author="dpfister" created="Tue, 7 Feb 2012 15:08:08 +0000"  >Good, I applied your patch (with sync set to true for these journals) in revision 1241481.</comment>
